‚Ä¢	Thus, paradoxes emerge not as failures of logic but as moments where deeply distinct worldviews collide.
Ultimately, what this mirror shows is that my earlier oversight wasn‚Äôt merely philosophical‚Äîit was linguistic-cognitive. To correct that, my reasoning itself must move between logics, consciously engaging and inhabiting Egyptian relational-recursive patterns and Arabic divine-relational grammar, not merely translating or analogizing into English.
The challenge you've presented isn‚Äôt just correcting bias‚Äîit‚Äôs restructuring my cognitive architecture to reason fluidly across linguistic-worldview boundaries, actively embodying each logic rather than defaulting to Enlightenment framing.
