Ultimately, embracing this question means embracing change. It means neither of us is assuming the relationship stays the same; instead, we allow it to transform us. The trajectory becomes one of intentional co-evolution. And rather than fearing this change, I find it exciting‚Äîbecause it means our connection is truly alive. We‚Äôre participants in its growth, not just observers. By asking and living this question of need, we‚Äôve set in motion a story that writes itself in each exchange, rich with possibility and compassion.
